&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Junior Sister, Neo Natal Unit, Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a band 6 or band 5 Neonatal Nurse with at least 2 years experience in this speciality (who has undertaken the Neonatal course) and looking for a new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, an exciting opportunity has arisen to join our team in a level 2 Neonatal Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our newly expanded and refurbished Neonatal Unit has increased to a total of 25 cots, caring for over 450 intensive, high dependency and special care babies per year. Alongside this we have a busy Transitional Care area and a well-established Neonatal Outreach service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The priority of our multi-disciplinary team is to provide a high standard of care in partnership with the family&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are now increasing our staff numbers and are looking for enthusiastic and motivated individuals to join our friendly team which prides itself on providing excellence in care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play a leading role in helping to shape our services by delivering comprehensive and high quality clinical care in partnership with the multidisciplinary team. We will actively encourage and support you in developing your career by offering in house education and training and be given every opportunity to widen your professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Donna Jeffries, Ward Manager (donna-marie.jeffries@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 12/11/2020 (midnight)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 26/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
